Hi Chase,

The crawler beans look okay, so it could be that the cor=
rect exchange and/or queue binding isn&#39;t set up in RabbtMQ. Since your craw=
ler beans are setting the `exchange` and `routingKey` properties to non-def=
aults, did you run umbra using the exchange and routing key you defined? If=
 you run umbra with flags as &quot;--exchange heritrix --routing-key phantomjs-d=
omain&quot; before launching the crawl, it should create the needed exchange and=
 queue binding for you. Similarly, the defaults of umbra and Heritrix align=
, so, if you don&#39;t care about setting those properties differently, you cou=
ld leave the `exchange` and `routingKey` properties out of the crawler bean=
s and start umbra with the defaults before the crawl is launched, and it sh=
ould create the default &#39;umbra&#39; exchange and  &#39;urls&#39; queue with appropriate=
 binding automatically.



